00:50.796 --> 00:51.997
Heil Hitler!

00:51.999 --> 00:53.632
Heil Hitler!

01:51.939 --> 01:53.940
'Fraid I can't do that,
old chap.

01:58.247 --> 01:59.080
Excuse me.

01:59.082 --> 02:00.849
[Blows land]

02:17.910 --> 02:21.614
A bit more violent
than I expected.

02:22.177 --> 02:23.011
Uh, bad luck.

02:26.048 --> 02:27.015
Could've used a warning

02:27.017 --> 02:28.884
before you fired
that Cannon.

02:28.886 --> 02:30.619
Sorry, Nigel.
Things were heating up.

02:30.621 --> 02:32.088
You all right?

02:32.090 --> 02:33.557
Fine.

02:33.559 --> 02:35.826
Bloody freezing country,
though, isn't it?

02:35.828 --> 02:39.130
Welcome to France.

02:44.104 --> 02:48.104
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Sanctuary 3x17 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Normandy</font>
Original Air Date on May 23, 2010

02:48.129 --> 02:52.129
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00ff00>elderman</font> ==

02:52.315 --> 02:55.383
Ludicrous, parading
around Nazi France alone.

02:55.416 --> 02:57.950
Should've brought some
bloody SAS lads for safety.

02:57.952 --> 03:00.485
More men means attracting
more attention.

03:00.487 --> 03:02.520
Unlike blowing up a
checkpoint with a tank.

03:02.522 --> 03:04.622
Well, if your German
sounded more Bavarian...

03:04.624 --> 03:05.690
Pish-posh.

03:05.692 --> 03:07.525
Shh.

03:09.862 --> 03:10.795
Thunder?

03:10.797 --> 03:11.830
Flash.

03:16.769 --> 03:18.203
I am Jeanette
Anaise,

03:18.205 --> 03:20.873
leader of the resistance
for this sector.

03:20.875 --> 03:22.608
Helen Magnus.

03:22.610 --> 03:24.644
James Watson,
Nigel Griffin.

03:24.646 --> 03:25.645
<i>Enchante.</i>

03:25.647 --> 03:26.880
Time is of the essence,
I'm afraid.

03:26.882 --> 03:29.316
We've only a few hours
to achieve our objective.

03:29.318 --> 03:30.951
You got our coded messages.

03:30.953 --> 03:32.553
I take it sabotage
is already underway.

03:32.555 --> 03:33.821
<i>La resistance</i>
<i>has begun</i>

03:33.823 --> 03:35.656
cutting power
and destroying rail lines,

03:35.658 --> 03:36.891
but what we do not know

03:36.893 --> 03:38.860
is when this invasion
will come.

03:38.862 --> 03:40.161
That depends on us, actually.

03:40.163 --> 03:42.263
General Eisenhower's
awaiting our signal.

03:42.265 --> 03:43.664
According to intelligence,

03:43.666 --> 03:45.966
there's an installation
near Varreville,

03:45.968 --> 03:46.901
a key
to Hitler's Atlantic Wall.

03:46.903 --> 03:48.802
How so?

03:48.804 --> 03:50.503
[Watson]: It apparently
houses a new technology

03:50.505 --> 03:52.038
developed by the Nazis,

03:52.040 --> 03:53.506
one they intend to deploy
against any approaching armada.

03:53.508 --> 03:54.407
[Magnus]:
Have you noticed

03:54.409 --> 03:56.809
any odd weather
patterns locally?

03:56.811 --> 03:58.277
As you can see,

03:58.279 --> 04:00.513
the trees have begun
to turn months early,

04:00.515 --> 04:02.348
there are failed crops
on every farm,

04:02.350 --> 04:06.686
and it rains for
hours every day.

04:06.688 --> 04:08.554
What have they created?

04:11.024 --> 04:14.460
She might as well
know the truth.

04:14.462 --> 04:16.462
We believe the SS
possess a device

04:16.464 --> 04:18.564
that can change
the weather.

04:18.565 --> 04:19.765
They could create
massive storms

04:19.767 --> 04:20.766
that could scuttle

04:20.767 --> 04:22.301
any landing attempts
on the beaches.

04:22.303 --> 04:23.936
From one device?

04:23.938 --> 04:26.872
Likely powered by a hive
of thermal sand rays

04:26.874 --> 04:28.040
to provide the energy
to power it.

04:28.042 --> 04:29.775
<i>Pardon?</i>

04:29.777 --> 04:30.776
Subterranean
desert creatures.

04:30.778 --> 04:33.912
They live off geothermal.

04:33.914 --> 04:36.514
We should know...
we deal with monsters.

04:36.516 --> 04:38.516
I deal with Nazis.

04:38.518 --> 04:39.851
I'd say we're even.

04:39.853 --> 04:41.787
Ha! I like this girl.

04:41.789 --> 04:42.954
We need to get
to Varreville,

04:42.956 --> 04:44.723
find the device,
and disable it.

04:44.725 --> 04:46.592
Otherwise, the invasion
will fail.

04:46.594 --> 04:48.460
Varreville is close.
I can take you there.

04:48.462 --> 04:50.896
It's a little more
complicated than that.

04:50.898 --> 04:51.930
We also need to find

04:51.932 --> 04:54.299
the latest schematics
for this machine.

04:54.301 --> 04:55.301
The word is the SS

04:55.303 --> 04:56.535
are keeping the
plans for the device

04:56.537 --> 04:58.637
in a town called Carentan.

04:58.639 --> 04:59.805
Is that a problem?

04:59.807 --> 05:03.709
The Gestapo have built
an underground bunker

05:03.711 --> 05:05.577
beneath this town.

05:05.579 --> 05:08.313
Many of my men have been taken
there for interrogation.

05:08.315 --> 05:09.580
None have come out.

05:09.582 --> 05:12.884
Carentan is
a very bad place.

05:22.093 --> 05:23.561
If that's more
chamomile tea,

05:23.563 --> 05:26.097
you can pour it
down the toilet.

05:26.099 --> 05:28.801
The kitchen says we're
out of black tea.

05:28.803 --> 05:30.235
Why?

05:30.237 --> 05:32.638
Because China was
invaded by Japan.

05:32.640 --> 05:35.608
Excuses.

05:35.610 --> 05:38.444
Still no word
from Dr. Magnus?

05:38.446 --> 05:39.779
Ugh.

05:39.781 --> 05:42.949
Worse than your coffee.

05:42.951 --> 05:45.552
You think they've
been captured?

05:45.554 --> 05:46.686
More that Helen
wasn't listening

05:46.688 --> 05:49.388
when I explained
how my autotype works.

05:49.390 --> 05:50.856
I'm sure they're fine.

05:50.858 --> 05:52.057
I should have
gone with them.

05:52.059 --> 05:54.992
As you know,
General Eisenhower's orders

05:54.994 --> 05:56.027
are to shoot you

05:56.029 --> 05:58.029
if you try and
get on a plane.

05:58.031 --> 05:59.197
Not that it would
really stop you,

05:59.199 --> 06:01.532
you being a vampire,
and all.

06:02.968 --> 06:05.036
Bad coffee,
English food,

06:05.038 --> 06:06.505
and worse, stuck here

06:06.507 --> 06:09.041
with the Kansas State
Glee Club.

06:09.043 --> 06:10.409
Come on, sir.

06:10.411 --> 06:11.677
Working for Allied Command
isn't so bad, is it?

06:11.679 --> 06:12.979
I work alone.

06:12.981 --> 06:15.748
But you cracked
the enigma code.

06:15.750 --> 06:16.883
It changed the tide
of the entire war.

06:16.885 --> 06:17.851
It did, didn't it?

06:17.853 --> 06:18.952
I'm just saying,

06:18.954 --> 06:21.121
you're doing
great things here, sir.

06:21.123 --> 06:25.058
The Japanese
invasion of China...

06:25.060 --> 06:26.860
What was the
inciting incident?

06:26.862 --> 06:31.064
The Marco Polo Bridge incident
of '37, wasn't it, sir?

06:31.066 --> 06:34.167
According to the war
department, yes.

06:34.169 --> 06:35.636
Or I could tell you
the truth...

06:35.638 --> 06:36.737
[Pop]

06:36.739 --> 06:38.973
[Watson]: The Wehrmacht
352nd infantry

06:38.975 --> 06:42.109
control the town.

06:42.111 --> 06:44.011
About a hundred men,

06:44.013 --> 06:46.413
likely all to protect
SS operations

06:46.415 --> 06:49.149
in the bunker
below ground.

06:49.151 --> 06:50.884
There's only
the one entrance?

06:50.886 --> 06:52.186
Two.

06:52.188 --> 06:53.186
One is from
the mayor's office,

06:53.188 --> 06:55.689
the other is just below
Cafe Normandie.

06:55.691 --> 06:56.757
Well, I'd vote
for the cafe

06:56.759 --> 06:58.125
rather than the
mayor's office.

06:58.127 --> 06:59.860
<i>Exactement.</i>

06:59.862 --> 07:01.896
We should be able to enter
completely undetected.

07:01.898 --> 07:03.998
[Click]

07:04.000 --> 07:06.134
Run!

07:06.136 --> 07:09.136
Bloody hell.

07:09.138 --> 07:10.738
[Firing]

07:19.515 --> 07:21.015
They knew
we were coming!

07:21.017 --> 07:22.750
That's impossible.

07:22.752 --> 07:24.051
My people would
not ever betray us.

07:24.053 --> 07:25.719
Well someone did!

07:38.967 --> 07:42.002
[Honking]

07:42.004 --> 07:44.706
Get in! Get in!

07:44.708 --> 07:47.510
Well done, Nigel!

07:47.512 --> 07:48.611
[Watson]: Grenade!

07:52.249 --> 07:53.116
James!

07:53.118 --> 07:54.217
Go! Go! Go!

07:54.219 --> 07:55.052
No, dammit!

07:55.054 --> 07:56.019
Go! I'll hold them off.

08:02.827 --> 08:04.094
[Clicking]

08:11.703 --> 08:14.037
Guten tag, Herr Watson.

08:14.039 --> 08:16.940
I am Colonel Franz Korba.

08:16.942 --> 08:19.176
The Fuhrer's is going to be
so happy to finally meet you.

08:21.179 --> 08:22.713
However, before that
wondrous event,

08:22.715 --> 08:25.250
we need some information
about the upcoming invasion.

08:29.022 --> 08:32.991
You should have stayed in
England with Professor Tesla.

08:44.705 --> 08:48.875
Dammit, they must've taken him
to the bunker already.

08:48.877 --> 08:51.311
[Jeanette]: We must leave here
right now.

08:51.313 --> 08:53.746
[Magnus]: Wait.

08:58.751 --> 09:00.553
Dear God.

09:01.889 --> 09:04.858
[Voices
in the corridor]

09:04.860 --> 09:08.228
Ah. Our guest has arrived.

09:08.230 --> 09:10.798
Oh, I'm sure I'll
be very impressed.

09:10.800 --> 09:12.967
I'm certain of it.

09:17.273 --> 09:18.808
Heil Hitler.

09:30.122 --> 09:32.924
James.

09:32.926 --> 09:34.592
You're looking well.

09:38.997 --> 09:42.634
I see you've finally found
a country to call home.

09:42.636 --> 09:45.803
National Socialism suits you.

09:45.805 --> 09:49.807
It's the attire.
Couldn't resist.

09:49.809 --> 09:52.644
Oh, Johnny, you really are
playing a delicious game

09:52.646 --> 09:55.346
with them,
aren't you?

09:56.882 --> 09:58.549
Did you never think it was odd

09:58.551 --> 10:00.618
that a man
born in the age of Victoria

10:00.620 --> 10:04.054
could have remained
so... spry?

10:04.056 --> 10:06.489
Oh, he does the most
unspeakable things to his blood.

10:06.491 --> 10:08.058
That is, of course,

10:08.060 --> 10:12.494
when he's not stealing it from
others in the dark of the night.

10:12.496 --> 10:14.663
And what of you,
James?

10:14.665 --> 10:20.936
Shall we share your secret
of eternal middle age?

10:20.938 --> 10:22.503
Spymaster...

10:22.505 --> 10:23.671
Detective...

10:25.374 --> 10:26.507
Inventor...

10:28.743 --> 10:30.877
Genius.

10:32.713 --> 10:34.114
You see, the problem is,

10:34.116 --> 10:40.721
a man who's lived
as long as Dr. James Watson

10:40.723 --> 10:43.157
never fears death.

10:43.159 --> 10:44.025
John...

10:44.027 --> 10:45.427
Don't.

10:45.429 --> 10:48.164
[Click]

10:57.942 --> 10:59.008
[Stifles a groan]

10:59.010 --> 11:00.176
The invasion landing
site.

11:00.178 --> 11:03.179
How many ships?

11:03.181 --> 11:05.114
How many men?

11:08.018 --> 11:12.756
You know what it is
we want to hear.

11:14.626 --> 11:17.028
[Choking sounds]

11:18.163 --> 11:20.498
Herr Druitt.

11:20.500 --> 11:23.100
Wait.

11:28.841 --> 11:31.476
[Choking]

11:33.746 --> 11:36.081
Hmm? Ah, yes.

11:39.051 --> 11:40.952
[Pushes button, Watson gasps]

11:43.455 --> 11:50.028
I know you're not
afraid to die, James.

11:50.030 --> 11:53.899
But I plan on making
you afraid to live.

12:02.909 --> 12:04.843
These communiques will
not be intercepted?

12:04.845 --> 12:06.511
Not from this.

12:06.513 --> 12:08.180
It uses a magnetic
sub frequency

12:08.182 --> 12:09.648
to speak
to its counterpart.

12:09.650 --> 12:12.651
Unless someone has one of these,
our messages are secure.

12:12.653 --> 12:14.086
[Troops and dogs approaching]

12:14.088 --> 12:14.953
[Gunfire]

12:14.955 --> 12:16.121
Come on!

12:16.123 --> 12:19.257
Never enough bloody time.

12:21.661 --> 12:25.564
Incoming message.

12:25.566 --> 12:27.233
Tell me good news.

12:33.506 --> 12:35.841
I need to talk to Eisenhower.
Right now.

12:40.213 --> 12:42.079
Stay with me, James.

12:42.081 --> 12:44.015
The night
is still young.

12:48.219 --> 12:51.087
He is not giving us much
concrete information.

12:51.089 --> 12:54.290
Patience. Hmm?

12:54.292 --> 12:55.825
Now, a man
in your condition

12:55.827 --> 12:56.826
would certainly never
be sent here alone.

12:56.828 --> 13:01.698
I know she's close by.

13:01.700 --> 13:03.132
The question is, why?

13:03.134 --> 13:04.334
What would cause the allies

13:04.336 --> 13:06.235
to send Helen Magnus
and James Watson

13:06.237 --> 13:09.572
together to France now?

13:09.574 --> 13:11.875
Resistance. Coordination.

13:11.877 --> 13:14.277
Lying, James?
Not a wise choice.

13:14.279 --> 13:16.680
[Dial clicks]

13:22.820 --> 13:23.787
Weather machine!

13:25.023 --> 13:27.324
We came... to stop it.

13:27.326 --> 13:29.726
[Turns dial down]

13:31.162 --> 13:32.396
The invasion?

13:32.398 --> 13:34.298
We will know everything
soon enough.

13:34.300 --> 13:35.666
Colonel Korba,
why don't you go

13:35.668 --> 13:38.034
and arrange for
Dr. Watson's transfer

13:38.036 --> 13:40.204
to Berlin.

13:43.575 --> 13:45.876
It was not a question, Colonel.

13:49.247 --> 13:50.113
[Clicks heels]

13:59.689 --> 14:01.023
This is useless.

14:01.025 --> 14:02.091
We're too easy
a target all together.

14:02.093 --> 14:03.793
We need to split up,
weaken the scent.

14:03.795 --> 14:05.061
You two stay together.

14:05.063 --> 14:06.930
I'll lead them off while you
drum up reinforcements.

14:06.932 --> 14:09.767
Nigel--

14:09.769 --> 14:10.968
He's the genius mind.

14:10.970 --> 14:12.169
You need him more
than you need me,

14:12.171 --> 14:14.239
and you know it.

14:14.241 --> 14:17.342
Just get him outta there before
they make him Hitler's houseboy.

14:20.246 --> 14:22.247
You are a very brave man,
monsieur.

14:27.321 --> 14:29.022
She likes me.

14:30.858 --> 14:31.992
Where the hell
have you been?

14:31.994 --> 14:33.126
It was difficult
to get a moment with him.

14:33.128 --> 14:34.127
He was in with Churchill
and DeGaulle--

14:34.129 --> 14:35.628
What
did he say?

14:35.630 --> 14:37.096
Did you show him
the message?

14:37.098 --> 14:39.132
General Eisenhower
appreciates your concern.

14:39.134 --> 14:40.966
Oh, that stubborn bastard.

14:40.968 --> 14:42.668
--Feels they cannot
delay the invasion

14:42.670 --> 14:44.336
because of one
fragmented message.

14:46.072 --> 14:48.406
This "fragment" represents
the gravest possible threat

14:48.408 --> 14:49.641
to retaking Europe.

14:49.643 --> 14:52.076
Jack the Ripper
in Nazi-held France?

14:52.078 --> 14:53.377
Do I have to paint
him a picture?

14:53.379 --> 14:55.012
Or should we just wait

14:55.014 --> 14:57.114
until Druitt teleports a bomb
into Churchill's office?

14:57.116 --> 14:58.315
Or the White House?

14:58.317 --> 14:59.283
I mean, they know this!

14:59.285 --> 15:01.151
It could mean
that Druitt is dead.

15:01.153 --> 15:02.019
Or on our side.

15:02.021 --> 15:03.688
Then get me a plane.

15:03.690 --> 15:05.290
Put me on a plane
and drop me in there

15:05.292 --> 15:06.224
with Helen and the others.

15:06.226 --> 15:08.759
Sir, that's not
going to happen.

15:08.761 --> 15:10.660
[Roaring]

15:13.497 --> 15:14.330
Excuse me.

15:14.332 --> 15:15.898
Where are you going?

15:15.900 --> 15:16.866
I'm going
to talk to Ike myself.

15:16.868 --> 15:17.767
Damn the protocols.

15:17.769 --> 15:20.003
Sir, you're too late.

15:20.005 --> 15:23.340
[Planes roar overhead]

15:33.885 --> 15:38.022
Those damn fools.

15:38.024 --> 15:39.690
[Jeanette]:
Why don't we just

15:39.692 --> 15:41.091
attack this
weather device

15:41.093 --> 15:42.192
and destroy it?

15:42.194 --> 15:43.026
[Magnus]: We can't.

15:43.028 --> 15:44.094
If we simply blow it up,

15:44.096 --> 15:45.028
the creatures they're
using to power it

15:45.030 --> 15:46.963
could do massive damage.

15:46.965 --> 15:48.097
You're certain?

15:48.099 --> 15:49.165
Of course.

15:49.167 --> 15:51.734
Unfortunately, it was
James who designed it.

15:51.736 --> 15:53.469
The schematics were
stolen eight months ago.

15:53.471 --> 15:55.905
We've been trying
to recover them since.

15:55.907 --> 15:57.173
Can he stop the weapon?

15:57.175 --> 15:58.274
That's why he's here.

15:58.276 --> 15:59.275
Unless they've made
modifications.

15:59.277 --> 16:01.111
[Planes approach]

16:01.113 --> 16:02.846
Helen...

16:02.848 --> 16:05.350
Do you hear that?

16:05.352 --> 16:06.952
The invasion...

16:06.954 --> 16:08.120
It's begun.

16:09.522 --> 16:13.959
[Air raid sirens wail]

16:35.780 --> 16:38.315
Whatever it is
you're playing at,

16:38.317 --> 16:40.184
I don't want to hear it.

16:43.890 --> 16:46.292
Get us out of here now.

16:46.294 --> 16:48.261
Do you want to destroy
the weather device?

16:48.263 --> 16:52.165
You need to listen.

16:52.167 --> 16:54.368
Even by your
standards.

16:54.370 --> 16:58.039
It is true, I have
no love for England,

16:58.041 --> 17:00.007
but I know evil
when I see it.

17:00.009 --> 17:01.475
In its purest form.

17:01.477 --> 17:06.381
I am working alone.
In my own way.

17:06.383 --> 17:08.249
Then why not kill Hitler?

17:08.251 --> 17:10.318
You could do that
in a heartbeat.

17:10.319 --> 17:12.053
And I did.
Nine months ago.

17:12.055 --> 17:13.954
At a lovely performance

17:13.957 --> 17:16.089
of Wagner's
<i>Tristan und Isolde</i> .

17:16.092 --> 17:18.059
His personal viewing box.

17:18.060 --> 17:20.929
I slid a blade right
through his tunic...

17:20.931 --> 17:23.298
felt his heart stop.

17:23.300 --> 17:24.500
Does it look like
it's made

17:24.502 --> 17:25.434
the slightest
difference?

17:25.435 --> 17:27.169
They're using body doubles.

17:27.171 --> 17:29.339
This Reich needs to be
taken apart piece by piece.

17:29.341 --> 17:32.109
One sordid element
at a time.

17:32.111 --> 17:34.311
You leaked information about
the weather machine. Why?

17:34.313 --> 17:36.547
I need you all here.

17:36.549 --> 17:39.350
The Fuhrer spent millions

17:39.352 --> 17:40.251
trying to find
abnormals

17:40.253 --> 17:41.952
to strengthen his army.

17:41.954 --> 17:43.154
Your machine...

17:43.156 --> 17:46.157
It's only a small part
of the plan.

17:46.159 --> 17:50.496
Something much
larger is at play.

17:54.000 --> 17:56.435
[Shouting in German]

18:24.361 --> 18:25.862
[Gunfire]

18:34.571 --> 18:36.272
Oh, hey!

18:36.274 --> 18:38.975
Hey, you all right,
pally?

18:38.977 --> 18:41.244
It's all right.
We're not gonna hurt ya.

18:41.246 --> 18:44.314
Uh, <i> parlez anglais?</i>

18:44.316 --> 18:48.486
Of course I do.
I'm English.

18:48.488 --> 18:49.520
Who the hell are you blokes?

18:49.522 --> 18:51.990
Americans.

18:51.992 --> 18:55.194
Cap, got a naked
limey over here.

18:55.196 --> 18:58.631
Well, don't that
beat all?

18:58.633 --> 19:00.300
Get the man a coat
or something, sergeant.

19:00.302 --> 19:03.402
Yeah, you got it.

19:05.238 --> 19:09.675
Looked like you needed
some help, friend.

19:09.677 --> 19:11.244
Captain Jack Zimmerman,

19:11.246 --> 19:14.447
Fox company,
101st Airborne.

19:14.449 --> 19:16.549
This country just got invaded.

19:21.146 --> 19:23.180
Yankee paratroopers
already?

19:23.182 --> 19:24.748
Well, we would have
dropped by last year,

19:24.750 --> 19:26.517
but there was that whole
North Africa problem.

19:26.519 --> 19:29.787
Yeah, and Italy.
That was fun.

19:29.789 --> 19:31.155
So what's your story?

19:31.157 --> 19:32.356
Aside from being, you know...
Clothes-less.

19:32.358 --> 19:34.692
I'm a British Agent
on a mission.

19:34.694 --> 19:36.127
There were three of us.
We got separated.

19:36.129 --> 19:37.094
Our leader,

19:37.096 --> 19:38.762
she's mustering the
local resistance.

19:38.764 --> 19:40.531
The other is being held
in Carentan.

19:40.533 --> 19:42.766
It's vital that we
get him out of there.

19:42.768 --> 19:43.634
Carentan?

19:44.703 --> 19:46.570
I don't think so, friend.

19:46.572 --> 19:49.106
Kraut 352nd infantry
owns that joint.

19:49.108 --> 19:51.042
Place is a damn stronghold.

19:51.044 --> 19:52.943
It'd be suicide.

19:52.945 --> 19:54.645
Stow all your jump gear.

19:54.647 --> 19:55.679
Weapons and ammo only.
We move out in five.

19:55.681 --> 19:57.180
Are you not listening?

19:57.182 --> 20:01.551
My orders are to link up
with the rest of the 506th

20:01.553 --> 20:04.487
and start clearing
causeway exits off Utah Beach.

20:04.489 --> 20:05.622
Which is that way.

20:05.624 --> 20:09.025
Trust me.
This is more important.

20:21.539 --> 20:23.040
Tell me
where I'm going.

20:23.042 --> 20:27.111
<i>La.</i> Four doors up on your right
is le Cafe Normandie.

20:27.113 --> 20:28.913
The entrance to the bunker
is in the back.

20:28.915 --> 20:31.049
Wait for my signal.

20:41.125 --> 20:42.258
No more games.

20:42.260 --> 20:44.827
Get. Us. Out.

20:44.829 --> 20:48.564
Well, you'll only kill me
the moment we rematerialize.

20:48.566 --> 20:50.199
That is a chance that
you'll have to take.

21:02.212 --> 21:04.047
You're with her now.

21:04.049 --> 21:06.216
Aren't you?

21:06.218 --> 21:08.651
I know you, old friend.

21:08.653 --> 21:11.521
Your passion...
Your passion for her,

21:11.523 --> 21:16.526
it just comes off you
like a bad smell.

21:16.528 --> 21:19.796
You leaked intelligence and
had us ambushed by the SS

21:19.798 --> 21:24.001
just so that you could
see her one more time.

21:24.003 --> 21:27.805
You are like a pathetic
schoolboy with a crush.

21:27.807 --> 21:29.574
I leaked
no such information,

21:29.576 --> 21:32.243
but it's very telling
that you think I would.

21:32.245 --> 21:37.314
No, John.
Do not dig too deeply.

21:37.316 --> 21:39.049
You don't know
how much you've hurt her.

21:39.051 --> 21:41.251
Hurt her?

21:41.253 --> 21:42.319
Or you?

21:52.998 --> 21:55.733
Feel better?

21:55.735 --> 21:57.736
Much.

21:57.738 --> 21:59.805
Shall we?

21:59.807 --> 22:00.639
God, yes.

22:10.984 --> 22:12.184
<i>Bonsoir.</i>

22:47.151 --> 22:48.685
[Korba]: I can vouch
for her identity.

22:51.089 --> 22:52.289
Dr. Magnus.

22:54.893 --> 22:56.193
Maybe it's something
about this place,

22:56.195 --> 23:01.898
the mineral content
of the walls.

23:01.900 --> 23:03.099
Perhaps it disrupts

23:03.101 --> 23:05.268
your ability to
convert to pure energy.

23:05.270 --> 23:08.037
Safe to say they know.

23:13.911 --> 23:14.745
Helen.

23:14.747 --> 23:17.148
Unbelievable.

23:17.150 --> 23:19.885
Let me alleviate some
of your confusion.

23:19.887 --> 23:21.386
This bunker is made
of lodestone,

23:21.388 --> 23:24.023
which naturally emits
a low-frequency form

23:24.025 --> 23:25.591
of electromagnetic
radiation.

23:25.593 --> 23:28.161
<i>Ja,</i> we have been
observing your abilities,

23:28.163 --> 23:29.262
Herr Druitt,

23:29.264 --> 23:30.930
and such power requires
a failsafe, no?

23:32.966 --> 23:34.300
We have enjoyed your services,

23:34.302 --> 23:36.202
however, all good things
must come to an end.

23:36.204 --> 23:38.704
Tell that to Hitler.

23:38.706 --> 23:40.239
Why don't you?

23:40.241 --> 23:41.774
[Fires]

23:41.776 --> 23:45.177
John!

23:45.179 --> 23:46.778
You did high command
a favor.

23:46.780 --> 23:49.280
The Furher's double is
easier to deal with.

23:49.282 --> 23:50.915
The Reich
is stronger for it.

23:50.917 --> 23:52.917
<i>Dankeschoen.</i>

23:54.753 --> 23:56.421
[Gives order in German]

24:04.065 --> 24:08.735
Now the person that I would
most like to talk with is...you.

24:10.772 --> 24:13.407
I appreciate your
orders, Captain,

24:13.409 --> 24:15.408
but if we don't deal
with this secret weapon,

24:15.410 --> 24:19.746
none of your countrymen
will make it ashore alive.

24:19.748 --> 24:22.983
Sounds like some weapon.

24:22.985 --> 24:24.751
How's it work?

24:27.455 --> 24:31.858
It's a weather machine
to scuttle the armada.

24:31.860 --> 24:33.126
What, like a death
ray or something?

24:33.128 --> 24:34.294
Or you mean
like in the comic books?

24:34.296 --> 24:36.796
Look, I don't know
how it works,

24:36.798 --> 24:38.765
I wasn't paying attention,
but the threat is real,

24:38.767 --> 24:40.200
and we were sent here
to stop it.

24:40.202 --> 24:42.102
We have orders,

24:42.104 --> 24:43.036
so unless you can
call up Ike

24:43.038 --> 24:44.771
and get them changed,

24:44.773 --> 24:47.173
we're headed
to the coast.

24:47.175 --> 24:49.442
Let's move out.

24:49.444 --> 24:52.178
I can make contact
with England.

24:52.180 --> 24:53.447
Impossible.

24:53.449 --> 24:55.449
I-corps declared a radio
silence over the channel

24:55.451 --> 24:57.484
before we left.

24:57.486 --> 24:58.452
There's a way.

24:58.454 --> 25:00.354
He's a hunted
criminal in Britain.

25:00.356 --> 25:02.289
Why not become
a Nazi Agent?

25:02.291 --> 25:04.758
The enemy of my enemy
is my friend.

25:04.760 --> 25:06.293
No, no, no,
I know John.

25:06.295 --> 25:08.095
He has no love
for any country.

25:08.097 --> 25:11.365
Then why show up in France
all of a sudden?

25:11.367 --> 25:12.800
Well, Johnny has
his own set of rules,

25:12.802 --> 25:14.335
which he rarely
deviates from.

25:14.337 --> 25:16.537
You mean his love for killing
innocent people.

25:16.539 --> 25:18.405
No, his love for Helen.

25:18.407 --> 25:20.474
He'd never let her come to harm,
not intentionally.

25:20.476 --> 25:21.708
But Dr. Magnus

25:21.710 --> 25:23.844
has been behind
enemy lines a dozen times.

25:23.846 --> 25:25.245
Why show up this time?

25:25.247 --> 25:28.247
I don't know.
He's a psychotic killer.

25:28.249 --> 25:29.782
But he's no Nazi.

25:29.784 --> 25:30.783
[Machine springs to life]

25:41.263 --> 25:42.297
"Druitt is a Nazi."

25:43.800 --> 25:44.900
"...has captured Watson.

25:44.902 --> 25:46.969
Magnus missing in action.

25:46.971 --> 25:50.306
Am with 101st Airborne
under a Captain J. Zimmerman.

25:50.308 --> 25:52.041
Have evaded detection so far.

25:52.043 --> 25:55.111
Please advise. Griffin."

25:55.113 --> 25:56.212
Take this to Eisenhower,

25:56.214 --> 25:57.513
and if he says
that it's cryptic,

25:57.515 --> 25:59.148
I'll knock his teeth in.

25:59.150 --> 26:00.149
Now go.

26:00.151 --> 26:01.083
Yes, sir.

26:05.422 --> 26:08.858
It's the craziest
looking thing.

26:08.860 --> 26:12.329
At least allied command
will know the situation.

26:12.331 --> 26:14.298
If you say so.

26:14.300 --> 26:16.066
Thank you, Captain,
for getting me this far.

26:16.068 --> 26:19.370
Don't mention it.

26:19.372 --> 26:21.005
So you're off, then?

26:21.007 --> 26:22.507
Utah Beach. You?

26:22.509 --> 26:25.977
Uh, Carentan.
I have to try.

26:25.979 --> 26:29.414
Yeah, well, try and
keep your clothes on.

26:29.416 --> 26:32.884
Unlikely.

26:32.886 --> 26:35.887
You really think command'll
turn back the armada?

26:35.889 --> 26:38.089
Well, if they're
smart, they will.

26:38.091 --> 26:39.390
The weapon's still active.

26:39.392 --> 26:40.925
The landings will fail
unless we knock it out.

26:40.927 --> 26:43.627
And only this Watson fella
knows how to do this.

26:43.629 --> 26:45.428
'Fraid so.

26:45.430 --> 26:47.430
Carentan, huh?

26:47.432 --> 26:49.365
I can get help.

26:53.904 --> 26:55.972
[Zimmerman]:
Damn shooting gallery.

27:02.013 --> 27:03.714
Place is tighter'n
a Berlin rally, Captain.

27:03.716 --> 27:04.548
Krauts for days.

27:04.550 --> 27:05.917
There's no telling

27:05.919 --> 27:08.119
how long they'll keep them
both alive down there.

27:08.121 --> 27:10.021
With reinforcements,
there's got to be a way in.

27:10.023 --> 27:11.422
No offense
to your people, ma'am,

27:11.424 --> 27:13.157
but there's no way
we have enough men

27:13.159 --> 27:15.091
to bust a guy out of
an underground bunker.

27:15.093 --> 27:16.660
Not without a bloodbath.

27:16.662 --> 27:19.362
We only need to
create a distraction.

27:19.364 --> 27:20.696
Nigel will do the rest.

27:20.698 --> 27:23.499
Naked fella here?
That I'd like to see.

27:25.301 --> 27:26.368
Well, that's the tricky part,
isn't it?

27:28.638 --> 27:30.272
What the hell, man?

27:30.274 --> 27:32.407
Holy mother of God!

27:32.409 --> 27:33.375
Well, I'll be.

27:33.377 --> 27:36.111
Better than a comic book?

27:36.113 --> 27:38.314
Yeah.

27:38.316 --> 27:40.616
Why bother gathering
intelligence from us?

27:40.618 --> 27:42.919
You have the ultimate weapon
at your disposal.

27:42.921 --> 27:46.390
We don't wish
to destroy Europe,

27:46.392 --> 27:48.358
we only wish to conquer it.

27:51.329 --> 27:52.997
The invasion is set
for Norway.

27:52.999 --> 27:57.334
We came here to deal with
your weather machine,

27:57.336 --> 27:59.370
in case it threatened
future operations.

28:01.973 --> 28:03.607
I think...
I think you are bluffing.

28:03.609 --> 28:07.010
And bluffing
is an American concept.

28:07.012 --> 28:10.580
I am disappointed to see you
engage in that.

28:12.349 --> 28:16.553
You know, in Berlin,
in the Reich,

28:16.555 --> 28:19.155
I am you, Helen.

28:19.157 --> 28:21.057
May I call you Helen?

28:21.059 --> 28:23.259
Absolutely not.

28:27.565 --> 28:29.667
I command the <i> SS Ahnenerbe.</i>

28:31.002 --> 28:33.438
No doubt you have heard of us.

28:33.440 --> 28:36.107
Hitler's
abnormal hunting division.

28:36.109 --> 28:39.378
<i>Ja.</i> Very much so.

28:39.380 --> 28:42.482
We find and we capture...

28:42.484 --> 28:45.485
Beings with
powerful abnormalities

28:45.487 --> 28:46.720
to serve the Fatherland.

28:46.722 --> 28:48.589
That's an odd agenda

28:48.591 --> 28:51.092
for the champions
of racial purity.

28:51.094 --> 28:53.327
You know, let me be clear.

28:53.329 --> 28:54.561
I am not going to be the one
who kills you.

28:54.563 --> 28:55.596
That will probably

28:55.598 --> 28:58.799
be some nameless
interrogator in Berlin.

28:58.801 --> 29:00.667
I just wanted to meet you.

29:00.669 --> 29:03.036
I am such a big
fan of yours, Helen.

29:03.038 --> 29:04.471
And of yours, Dr. Watson.

29:06.007 --> 29:07.140
Not only because of

29:07.142 --> 29:09.009
your exploits
in the war.

29:09.011 --> 29:11.444
No.

29:11.446 --> 29:14.681
I admire...

29:14.683 --> 29:16.316
Your stamina.

29:16.318 --> 29:20.521
You are both
over 80 years old.

29:20.523 --> 29:23.457
And I will not let
either one of you rest

29:23.459 --> 29:25.626
until I know the reasons why.

29:27.329 --> 29:30.030
Your retinas
are burned.

29:30.032 --> 29:31.732
There's only one creature
on Earth

29:31.734 --> 29:33.300
that could cause
that exact injury.

29:33.302 --> 29:37.104
<i>Ja.</i> Oh, and
it was worth it.

29:37.106 --> 29:38.339
You're not dealing
with sand rays.

29:38.341 --> 29:40.808
You have
a Tunisian fire elemental.

29:40.810 --> 29:42.310
That's the real weapon.

29:42.312 --> 29:44.678
You needed the
weather machine...

29:44.680 --> 29:46.280
to control it.

29:46.282 --> 29:49.683
To keep it calm
until you unleash it.

29:49.685 --> 29:51.518
[Laughs] That's right.

29:51.520 --> 29:53.187
It was your invention

29:53.189 --> 29:56.757
that provided the final
piece to the puzzle.

29:56.759 --> 29:58.058
And with that,
now I can control

29:58.060 --> 30:00.528
the most powerful creature
in history.

30:00.530 --> 30:04.298
Not only
will your invasion fail...

30:04.300 --> 30:09.235
<i>You will lose the war.</i>

30:45.315 --> 30:47.750
First six on me.

30:57.162 --> 30:59.096
Sergeant.

30:59.098 --> 31:00.897
See those barrels,
12 o'clock?

31:00.899 --> 31:01.798
It's a good
firing position

31:01.800 --> 31:03.300
to cover
from the street.

31:03.302 --> 31:05.702
Take Dunne with you,
and that slapjack.

31:05.704 --> 31:07.304
And extra ammo.

31:07.306 --> 31:08.171
I'm on it, cap.

31:30.628 --> 31:32.628
What makes you think
you can control it?

31:32.630 --> 31:34.297
Well, you see,

31:34.299 --> 31:36.132
there are ancient texts
of the Phoenicians

31:36.134 --> 31:38.368
that describe this powerful
fiery beast

31:38.370 --> 31:40.303
that killed thousands
of their enemies,

31:40.305 --> 31:44.375
and then it went back
to its habitat, satiated.

31:44.377 --> 31:45.743
Ancient texts?

31:45.745 --> 31:48.280
You're basing this
all on legend?

31:48.282 --> 31:49.748
We uncovered
the creature.

31:49.750 --> 31:52.251
Under Tunis, one year ago.

31:52.253 --> 31:55.288
Perfectly preserved in a tomb.

31:55.290 --> 31:56.856
You have no idea

31:56.858 --> 31:58.024
what you're
actually dealing with.

31:58.026 --> 32:00.026
A fire elemental
can't be contained

32:00.028 --> 32:02.061
once it's been unleashed.

32:02.063 --> 32:03.929
You can't simply call it
back with a dog whistle.

32:03.931 --> 32:07.032
It will continue
to consume fuel

32:07.034 --> 32:08.333
and oxygen,

32:08.335 --> 32:11.670
for weeks, for months,
before it rests.

32:11.672 --> 32:15.440
Your master-stroke
has doomed the Reich.

32:15.442 --> 32:17.909
And probably the world.

32:17.911 --> 32:22.982
What button was it
that Herr Druitt pushed?

32:22.984 --> 32:23.816
[Cries out]

32:34.129 --> 32:34.962
[Kicks a piece of metal]

32:42.370 --> 32:44.237
[Gunshot]

32:44.239 --> 32:45.806
[Gunfire]

32:45.808 --> 32:47.807
The jig is up!

32:54.114 --> 32:56.048
[Gunshot]

32:56.050 --> 32:58.851
I hope your boyfriend's
right about this place!

33:04.959 --> 33:06.794
Covering fire!

33:08.130 --> 33:09.764
Move!

33:25.348 --> 33:26.882
[A blow lands]

33:40.264 --> 33:41.364
Helen?

33:44.268 --> 33:45.101
No.

33:54.946 --> 33:55.780
James!

33:55.782 --> 33:57.148
James!

34:11.864 --> 34:13.097
This is goin' really well.

34:17.268 --> 34:18.802
[Whispering] Nigel? Nigel?

34:18.804 --> 34:19.969
Here.

34:25.944 --> 34:28.844
Thank God!
Nigel, help James!

34:30.581 --> 34:32.014
Thank you.

34:36.121 --> 34:37.821
Nigel, dear boy.

34:37.822 --> 34:39.922
Darling, are you all right?

34:41.159 --> 34:43.525
Schematics.
I need the schematics.

34:43.527 --> 34:44.360
They should be here.

34:48.031 --> 34:49.931
Professor?

35:03.480 --> 35:05.581
[Machine springs to life]

35:25.469 --> 35:28.871
Or just plain old
garden-variety greed?

35:28.873 --> 35:30.906
Huh?

35:34.044 --> 35:36.178
How long?

35:36.180 --> 35:40.416
I was recruited by the SS
when I was still at West Point.

35:40.418 --> 35:42.217
My family supports the Reich.

35:42.219 --> 35:43.552
It was my duty.

35:46.056 --> 35:48.491
You were good,
but I was better.

35:48.493 --> 35:50.492
How did you figure it out?

35:50.494 --> 35:51.927
Simple logic,
really.

35:51.929 --> 35:54.196
You see, Ike would never
have launched <i>Overlord</i>

35:54.198 --> 35:56.031
if he knew
that Druitt was in France.

35:56.033 --> 35:57.533
But then it suddenly
dawned on me:

35:57.535 --> 35:59.668
What if the good general
wasn't actually getting

35:59.670 --> 36:01.637
any of the information
I've been providing him with?

36:01.639 --> 36:04.206
Or worse,

36:04.208 --> 36:07.343
what if someone
tipped off the SS in Carentan

36:07.345 --> 36:10.646
about Helen
and her mission?

36:10.648 --> 36:15.719
Oh, you made me like you.

36:17.421 --> 36:18.354
He's ready.

36:21.191 --> 36:22.357
Professor...

36:22.359 --> 36:25.994
Enjoy your tribunal,
Lieutenant.

36:35.137 --> 36:37.071
[Gunfire]

36:51.288 --> 36:52.555
Go! Go!

36:55.426 --> 36:57.727
[Gunfire resumes]

37:18.646 --> 37:22.015
[Plane approaches]

37:28.556 --> 37:31.425
I found these grunts
looking for a fight.

37:31.427 --> 37:35.261
506th, Easy Company,
can't find their C.O.

37:48.141 --> 37:50.175
[Magnus]: 5:30.

37:50.177 --> 37:52.411
First wave of landings should
start in less than an hour,

37:52.413 --> 37:55.280
if they stick to the timetable.

37:55.282 --> 37:56.748
There it is.
Maintenance entrance.

38:00.086 --> 38:01.186
What's the plan?

38:01.188 --> 38:02.321
Kill or disable
the elemental

38:02.323 --> 38:03.556
without setting it off.

38:03.558 --> 38:04.757
Can you do it, James?

38:04.759 --> 38:07.394
Well, if you get me
inside, we have a chance.

38:07.396 --> 38:11.298
Well, it doesn't look
too hard.

38:11.300 --> 38:12.500
Something this important
I thought

38:12.502 --> 38:13.668
would be more heavily guarded.

38:13.670 --> 38:15.403
[Shell explodes]

38:35.478 --> 38:36.945
This is madness!
They've got tanks!

38:42.552 --> 38:45.421
[Planes approach]

38:49.626 --> 38:51.494
[Cries out]

38:52.663 --> 38:54.163
[Cries out]

38:58.001 --> 39:00.136
Wells! Halladay!
Get over that line!

39:00.138 --> 39:02.204
I want bazooka fire
on those tanks all day!

39:06.610 --> 39:07.676
We're going in!

39:07.678 --> 39:10.513
Keep them away
from the entrance!

39:10.515 --> 39:13.148
[Groaning]

39:17.754 --> 39:20.722
They're friendlies!
Covering fire!

39:40.175 --> 39:42.143
Oh, it's incredible.

39:45.514 --> 39:48.450
Oh... the climate
settings are all wrong!

39:48.452 --> 39:52.622
None of my safety protocols
are in place.

39:52.624 --> 39:54.090
James...

39:54.092 --> 39:56.626
There's one part of the legend
that's actually true.

39:58.329 --> 40:00.730
There's no way to really kill
a fire elemental.

40:00.732 --> 40:02.065
It's kind of

40:02.067 --> 40:04.568
why they call them
"elementals."

40:04.570 --> 40:06.236
You're telling me this now?

40:06.238 --> 40:09.239
[Shouting]

40:17.415 --> 40:19.650
It can't leave.

40:19.652 --> 40:21.619
Is there a way that
you can force it down?

40:23.321 --> 40:26.290
Air pressure change.

40:26.292 --> 40:29.259
I can create
massive wind shear.

40:29.261 --> 40:31.696
Literally bury it
in the Earth.

40:31.698 --> 40:32.930
Can you make that happen?

40:32.932 --> 40:36.767
It's not what it was
designed for, but...

40:38.536 --> 40:39.469
Hold on!

40:54.351 --> 40:56.052
N!

41:09.366 --> 41:10.634
[Materializing]

41:17.242 --> 41:19.710
[Laughs triumphantly]

41:39.733 --> 41:40.766
John.

41:40.768 --> 41:43.436
What have you done?

41:43.438 --> 41:45.838
What I always do.
What you can't.

41:48.342 --> 41:49.543
Treat her well,
James.

42:10.864 --> 42:11.931
Your commanding
officer.

42:15.768 --> 42:17.536
Yeah.

42:17.538 --> 42:18.971
One of the best.

42:22.276 --> 42:24.244
Thank you, sergeant.

42:24.246 --> 42:26.713
For this.

42:26.715 --> 42:29.583
It won't be forgotten.

